-- Colombia Stocks: Carvajal Empaques, Pacific Rubiales, Canacol
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-06-13T20:51:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/colombian-stocks-carvajal-empaques-fabricato-pacific-rubiales.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  was little changed at 13,899.07 while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  fell 0.2 percent to 1,653.02.  Carvajal Empaques SA (PFCARPAK)  , the packaging unit of
Colombian holding company Carvajal SA, rose 4.6 percent to 5,050
pesos. Carvajal Empaques was rated buy today in new coverage
from Helm Bank SA’s brokerage unit. The target price is 5,900
pesos per share.  Oil producers fell as crude tumbled to an eight-month low.
Crude oil for July delivery dropped to $82.62 a barrel in  New
York , the lowest settlement since Oct. 6.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , which operates the
country’s largest oil field, fell 0.3 percent to 43,100 pesos.
 Petrominerales Ltd. (PMG)  , a Calgary-based  oil company  that
operates in the Andean region, slid 1.7 percent to 21,200 pesos.
 Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE)  , the Calgary-based oil company
that operates fields in  Colombia , dropped 0.4 percent to pesos
996 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
